00:11.100 --> 00:15.033
<i>♪ YOU'RE A PAL</i>
<i>AND A CONFIDANTE ♪</i>

00:16.033 --> 00:20.033
<i>♪ AND IF YOU THREW A PARTY ♪</i>

00:20.100 --> 00:24.433
<i>♪ INVITED EVERYONE YOU KNEW ♪</i>

00:24.500 --> 00:28.834
<i>♪ YOU WOULD SEE</i>
<i>THE BIGGEST GIFT</i>
<i>WOULD BE FROM ME ♪</i>

00:28.900 --> 00:31.600
<i>♪ AND THE CARD ATTACHED</i>
<i>WOULD SAY ♪</i>

00:31.667 --> 00:37.467
<i>♪ "THANK YOU</i>
<i>FOR BEIN' A FRIEND" ♪</i>

00:55.800 --> 00:57.834
OH, YOU
COULDN'T SLEEP EITHER?

00:57.900 --> 00:58.867
NO.

00:58.934 --> 01:02.266
I CAN'T BELIEVE
MA'S REALLY GOING.

01:02.333 --> 01:04.934
I'VE TRIED
TO DISSUADE HER.

01:05.000 --> 01:06.800
SHE STILL INSISTS
SHE'S LEAVING.

01:06.867 --> 01:08.533
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO.

01:08.600 --> 01:11.900
LET ME GET THE CHEESECAKE,
AND WE'LL TALK.

01:11.967 --> 01:13.533
OH, MY GOD!

01:13.600 --> 01:14.567
WHAT'S WRONG?

01:14.633 --> 01:16.633
WE'RE IN THE MIDDLE
OF A CRISIS,

01:16.700 --> 01:18.867
AND THERE'S
NO CHEESECAKE.

01:18.934 --> 01:20.800
DIDN'T WE BUY ONE
YESTERDAY?

01:20.867 --> 01:24.467
YES, BUT I FOUND
TWO GRAY HAIRS.

01:24.533 --> 01:25.800
BLANCHE, YOU'RE OVER 50.

01:25.867 --> 01:27.867
FINDING TWO GRAY HAIRS

01:27.934 --> 01:30.300
IS NO REASON TO EAT
A WHOLE CHEESECAKE.

01:30.367 --> 01:31.767
I FOUND
THE TWO GRAY HAIRS

01:31.834 --> 01:33.900
IN THE CHEESECAKE...

01:33.967 --> 01:36.300
SO I THREW IT OUT.

01:36.367 --> 01:37.834
HI, GIRLS.

01:37.900 --> 01:40.467
I FIGURED
THIS MIGHT HAPPEN,

01:40.533 --> 01:42.600
SO I WENT OUT
AND BOUGHT A CHEESECAKE.

01:42.667 --> 01:44.100
OH, ROSE,
THAT'S GREAT!

01:44.166 --> 01:45.600
WHAT'S REALLY GREAT

01:45.667 --> 01:47.700
IS THEY FIRED
THAT GRAY-HAIRED BAKER

01:47.767 --> 01:50.667
WHO REFUSED
TO WEAR A NET.

01:50.734 --> 01:52.233
LET'S SLICE THIS UP

01:52.300 --> 01:54.967
AND SOLVE
OUR SOPHIA PROBLEM.

01:55.033 --> 01:56.300
HERE, DARLING.

01:56.367 --> 01:58.633
OH, DO YOU KNOW
HOW MANY PROBLEMS

01:58.700 --> 02:01.100
WE HAVE SOLVED
OVER A CHEESECAKE

02:01.166 --> 02:03.100
AT THIS KITCHEN TABLE?

02:03.166 --> 02:04.600
NO, DOROTHY. HOW MANY?

02:04.667 --> 02:06.867
147, ROSE!

02:12.133 --> 02:15.000
THE POINT I'M MAKING
IS THAT WE'VE HAD

02:15.066 --> 02:18.033
A LOT OF GREAT
LATE-NIGHT TALKS

02:18.100 --> 02:19.066
RIGHT HERE.

02:19.133 --> 02:21.700
MOST OF THEM
WERE ABOUT SEX.

02:21.767 --> 02:23.200
OH...WELL, OF COURSE,

02:23.266 --> 02:24.967
WE DO TALK ABOUT SEX,

02:25.033 --> 02:27.133
BUT WE DISCUSS
OTHER THINGS.

02:27.200 --> 02:28.567
WE CONSOLE EACH OTHER.

02:28.633 --> 02:29.567
WE HELP EACH OTHER.

02:29.633 --> 02:30.967
WE ADVISE EACH OTHER.

02:31.033 --> 02:33.867
AND THEN...WE TALK
ABOUT SEX AGAIN.

02:35.166 --> 02:39.166
I AM SO GLAD MY DATE
WITH BARRY IS TOMORROW.

02:39.233 --> 02:41.900
THE FAT WON'T HAVE
TIME TO SHOW.

02:41.967 --> 02:42.900
IT WON'T?

02:42.967 --> 02:45.533
IT TAKES SEVERAL DAYS.

02:45.600 --> 02:47.500
WHERE DOES IT GO
IN THE MEANTIME?

02:47.567 --> 02:48.500
TO CONNECTICUT!

02:48.567 --> 02:51.133
HOW DO I KNOW WHERE?

02:51.200 --> 02:54.500
THE MINUTE I EAT IT,
I BALLOON UP.

02:54.567 --> 02:55.834
I CAN GO
OUT TO DINNER

02:55.900 --> 02:57.133
AND DURING THE MEAL,

02:57.200 --> 02:59.266
MY PANTS
GET SO TIGHT,

02:59.333 --> 03:01.367
MY FEET TURN BLUE.

03:01.433 --> 03:05.500
I JUST WANT
TO BE SVELTE FOR BARRY.

03:05.567 --> 03:07.900
BARRY GLICK IS VERY
IMPORTANT TO YOU.

03:08.400 --> 03:14.633
BARRY WAS THE MAN THAT
I WANTED TO BE THE FIRST.

03:14.700 --> 03:16.066
FIRST WHERE?

03:16.133 --> 03:18.934
ON MARS, ROSE!

03:19.000 --> 03:20.867
MY FIRST LOVER.

03:20.934 --> 03:22.200
SO WHAT HAPPENED?

03:22.266 --> 03:24.700
STANLEY.
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

03:24.767 --> 03:25.900
STANLEY.

03:25.967 --> 03:28.667
I WENT TO A DRIVE-IN
WITH STANLEY.

03:28.734 --> 03:31.000
HE SAID HE WAS BEING
SHIPPED TO KOREA

03:31.066 --> 03:32.066
AND WOULD PROBABLY DIE,

03:32.133 --> 03:34.467
AND IT WOULD
MEAN SO MUCH.

03:34.533 --> 03:37.567
THAT WAS MY PART
OF THE WAR EFFORT.

03:39.233 --> 03:42.266
IT TOOK THREE SECONDS.

03:42.333 --> 03:46.400
I WASN'T SURE THAT WE HAD
DONE ANYTHING, ACTUALLY,

03:46.467 --> 03:49.400
UNTIL NINE MONTHS LATER
WHEN THE BABY CAME.

03:49.467 --> 03:52.233
THEN I FIGURED OUT
THAT WE HAD.

03:52.300 --> 03:54.800
YOU KNOW, THAT
WAS MY ONLY PROOF.

03:54.867 --> 03:57.300
I WAITED TILL
MY WEDDING NIGHT.

04:00.300 --> 04:02.033
NO!

04:02.100 --> 04:03.700
YES!

04:03.767 --> 04:05.333
AND?

04:05.400 --> 04:08.967
AND...IT WAS A SURPRISE.

04:09.033 --> 04:10.367
HOW IS THAT POSSIBLE?

04:10.433 --> 04:12.500
ANOTHER MAN SHOWED UP?

04:13.834 --> 04:15.867
WHAT I MEAN IS,

04:15.934 --> 04:20.066
I HAD NEVER...
SEEN A MAN BEFORE.

04:26.100 --> 04:27.467
A MAN?

04:27.533 --> 04:29.867
YOU KNOW--

04:29.934 --> 04:31.467
A MAN.

04:32.467 --> 04:34.000
NO.

04:34.066 --> 04:35.867
YES!

04:35.934 --> 04:37.333
WHAT ABOUT YOUR FATHER?

04:37.400 --> 04:38.700
YOU MEAN YOU NEVER...

04:38.767 --> 04:40.834
SAW YOUR FATHER?

04:40.900 --> 04:43.066
MY FATHER?

04:43.133 --> 04:44.667
OH, NO--MY FATHER?

04:44.734 --> 04:46.900
OH, MY GOODNESS, NO!

04:46.967 --> 04:48.233
I WOULD HAVE SIMPLY DIED!

04:48.300 --> 04:49.266
OH, YOU DON'T--

04:49.333 --> 04:50.300
EASY!

04:50.367 --> 04:53.934
ALL RIGHT!

04:54.000 --> 04:56.367
THE ONLY THINGS
I EVER SAW

04:56.433 --> 04:58.300
WERE ANIMALS
ON THE FARM--

04:58.367 --> 05:00.667
THE BULLS
AND THE HORSES.

05:00.734 --> 05:02.667
TOUGH ACT
TO FOLLOW.

05:11.233 --> 05:14.300
ACTUALLY,
THAT FIRST NIGHT...

05:14.367 --> 05:16.233
I WAS KIND OF...

05:16.300 --> 05:18.033
WELL...

05:18.100 --> 05:19.800
APPALLED, I GUESS.

05:19.867 --> 05:22.400
BUT CHARLIE
WAS VERY PATIENT.

05:22.467 --> 05:24.900
IT WAS REALLY VERY NICE...

05:24.967 --> 05:26.767
ONCE I UNDERSTOOD THAT

05:26.834 --> 05:29.767
THAT'S WHAT YOU
WERE SUPPOSED TO DO,

05:29.834 --> 05:32.333
AND IT WASN'T SOME
COLOSSAL JOKE.

05:35.233 --> 05:38.900
DIDN'T YOU THINK IT WAS
A RIDICULOUS THING TO DO

05:38.967 --> 05:40.033
THE FIRST TIME?

05:40.767 --> 05:42.633
NO!

05:44.500 --> 05:47.300
I CERTAINLY DIDN'T WAIT
FOR MY WEDDING NIGHT.

05:47.367 --> 05:50.934
I COULDN'T.
I HAD THESE URGES.

05:51.000 --> 05:53.600
YOU KNOW, IN THE SOUTH
WE MATURE FASTER.

05:53.667 --> 05:56.300
I THINK IT'S THE HEAT.

05:58.266 --> 06:00.967
I THINK IT'S THE GIN.

06:02.233 --> 06:05.433
ANYHOW, MY FIRST
WAS BILLY.

06:05.500 --> 06:07.333
OH, I REMEMBER IT
SO WELL,

06:07.400 --> 06:09.333
JUST LIKE
IT WAS YESTERDAY.

06:09.400 --> 06:11.667
THAT NIGHT, UNDER
THE DOGWOOD TREES,

06:11.734 --> 06:14.467
