GOING THROUGH THE CHANGE?

07:46.633 --> 07:48.166
GOD, I HATE THAT EXPRESSION.

07:48.233 --> 07:49.934
WHAT IS THE BIG DEAL, BLANCHE?

07:50.000 --> 07:51.300
IT'S NOTHING.

07:51.367 --> 07:54.667
LOOK AT IT THIS WAY, YOU DON'T
GET CRAMPS ONCE A MONTH.

07:54.734 --> 07:57.033
YOU DON'T GO ON EATING BINGES
ONCE A MONTH.

07:57.100 --> 07:58.934
YOU DON'T GET CRAZY
ONCE A MONTH.

07:59.000 --> 08:00.500
YOU JUST GROW A BEARD.

08:08.333 --> 08:09.967
DON'T LISTEN TO HER, BLANCHE.

08:10.033 --> 08:11.800
YOU GROW A BEARD,
DOROTHY, BELIEVE ME.

08:11.867 --> 08:13.667
I WOKE UP ONE MORNING,
I LOOKED LIKE ARAFAT.

08:13.734 --> 08:17.367
OH, MY GOD.

08:17.433 --> 08:19.033
I NEVER GREW A BEARD.

08:19.100 --> 08:21.800
YOU NEVER GREW BRAINS, EITHER.

08:22.667 --> 08:25.734
WELL, I TELL YOU MENOPAUSE
WAS WONDERFUL FOR ME.

08:25.800 --> 08:27.767
IT MEANT NO MORE PMS.

08:27.834 --> 08:29.200
I NEVER HAD PMS.

08:29.266 --> 08:30.333
NEITHER DID I.

08:30.400 --> 08:32.233
BUT I HAD A BMW.

08:35.266 --> 08:36.367
I'VE HAD IT!

08:36.433 --> 08:38.233
THANKS TO ALL
THIS BICKERING,

08:38.300 --> 08:39.734
I HAVE A HEADACHE.

08:39.800 --> 08:42.066
LET'S FACE FACTS--

08:42.133 --> 08:44.567
WE JUST CAN'T
AGREE ON ANYTHING.

08:44.633 --> 08:47.333
IT'S OBVIOUS WE WEREN'T
MEANT TO LIVE TOGETHER.

08:47.400 --> 08:48.834
I HATE TO AGREE,

08:48.900 --> 08:50.166
BUT I THINK
YOU'RE RIGHT.

08:50.233 --> 08:51.667
I THINK SO, TOO.

08:51.734 --> 08:53.567
IN FACT,
I KNOW SO.

08:53.633 --> 08:56.266
THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED

08:56.333 --> 08:58.233
DURING THE GREAT
HERRING WAR.

09:02.367 --> 09:04.734
THE GREAT HERRING WAR?

09:04.800 --> 09:07.066
BETWEEN THE LINDSTROMS
AND THE JOHANNSENS.

09:07.133 --> 09:09.967
OH, THAT GREAT
HERRING WAR!

09:11.000 --> 09:12.333
THE TWO FAMILIES

09:12.400 --> 09:14.233
CONTROLLED THE MOST
FERTILE HERRING WATERS

09:14.300 --> 09:15.767
OFF THE NORWEGIAN COAST,

09:15.834 --> 09:18.633
SO NATURALLY, IT SEEMED
IN THEIR BEST INTERESTS

09:18.700 --> 09:19.867
TO BAND TOGETHER.

09:19.934 --> 09:22.567
OH, BOY,
WAS THAT A MISTAKE!

09:22.633 --> 09:25.700
THEY DISAGREED ON WHAT
TO DO WITH THE HERRING.

09:25.767 --> 09:27.433
WELL, THAT'S
UNDERSTANDABLE.

09:27.500 --> 09:30.400
I MEAN,
THE POSSIBILITIES
ARE OVERWHELMING.

09:31.400 --> 09:32.600
EXACTLY.

09:32.667 --> 09:35.333
THE JOHANNSENS WANTED
TO PICKLE THE HERRING.

09:35.400 --> 09:38.567
THE LINDSTROMS WANTED TO
TRAIN THEM FOR THE CIRCUS.

09:41.367 --> 09:43.967
WEREN'T THEY KIND
OF HARD TO SEE,

09:44.033 --> 09:45.867
RIDING ON
THE ELEPHANTS?

09:46.967 --> 09:49.967
NOT THAT KIND OF CIRCUS.
A HERRING CIRCUS.

09:50.033 --> 09:51.934
SORT OF LIKE
SEA WORLD,

09:52.000 --> 09:53.333
ONLY SMALLER.

09:54.433 --> 09:56.867
MUCH, MUCH SMALLER.

09:56.934 --> 09:59.233
BUT BIGGER THAN
A FLEA CIRCUS.

09:59.300 --> 10:02.533
MM-HMM. TELL ME,
ROSE, UM...

10:05.166 --> 10:09.633
DID THEY EVER SHOOT
A HERRING OUT OF A CANNON?

10:19.467 --> 10:21.500
ONLY ONCE.

10:25.233 --> 10:28.033
BUT THEY SHOT HIM
INTO A TREE.

10:29.066 --> 10:32.667
AFTER THAT, NO OTHER
HERRING WOULD DO IT.

10:34.700 --> 10:37.333
YOU'RE MAKING
THIS UP.

10:37.400 --> 10:38.700
I AM NOT!

10:38.767 --> 10:42.200
MY GRANDFATHER
TOLD ME THAT STORY.

10:42.266 --> 10:46.700
OF COURSE,
HE ALSO CALLED ME
BY MY SISTER'S NAME.

10:46.767 --> 10:49.467
AND SOMETIMES
HE'D WEAR HIS UNDERWEAR

10:49.533 --> 10:50.767
ON THE OUTSIDE
OF HIS PANTS.

10:52.734 --> 10:56.400
I GUESS HE WASN'T
A VERY RELIABLE SOURCE.

10:58.367 --> 10:59.734
OH!

11:02.367 --> 11:03.967
OH, GIRLS, GIRLS,

11:04.033 --> 11:07.333
DO YOU REALIZE
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

11:07.400 --> 11:09.033
I'VE BEEN
HAVING FUN,

11:09.100 --> 11:10.800
AND THERE WASN'T
EVEN A MAN
IN THE ROOM.

11:14.033 --> 11:15.467
WAS IT A FLUKE,

11:15.533 --> 11:17.500
OR COULD WE GET ALONG?

11:17.567 --> 11:20.200
WELL, I THINK
IT MIGHT TAKE TIME,

11:20.266 --> 11:22.834
BUT IT COULD
BE WORTH IT.

11:22.900 --> 11:24.100
LET'S TRY!

11:24.166 --> 11:25.100
GREAT!

11:25.166 --> 11:26.633
I'M GAME.

11:32.967 --> 11:34.033
WAIT A MINUTE.

11:34.100 --> 11:35.200
WHAT'S THAT?

11:35.266 --> 11:36.567
OH, I'M SORRY.

11:36.633 --> 11:39.467
I HAVE THIS
INCREDIBLE SWEET TOOTH.

11:39.533 --> 11:41.867
WHAT IS IT?
CHOCOLATE CHEESECAKE.

11:41.934 --> 11:43.900
THIS COULD BE
THE BEGINNING

11:43.967 --> 11:45.700
OF A BEAUTIFUL
FRIENDSHIP.

11:47.734 --> 11:48.867
THIS IS UNHEARD OF.

11:48.934 --> 11:50.567
