13:56.467 --> 13:58.800
ROSE, PLAY OR DIE.

14:01.367 --> 14:03.333
♪ MIAMI IS NICE ♪

14:03.400 --> 14:05.600
♪ SO I'LL SAY IT TWICE ♪

14:05.667 --> 14:09.633
♪ MIAMI IS NICE
MIAMI IS NICE ♪

14:09.700 --> 14:10.934
♪ MIAMI-- ♪

14:11.000 --> 14:14.433
WAIT A MINUTE.
WAIT A MINUTE.

14:14.500 --> 14:17.300
YOU PUT IN AN EXTRA,
"MIAMI IS NICE".

14:17.367 --> 14:19.867
I HAD TO. IT HURTS THE MUSIC IF
YOU DON'T PUT IT IN.

14:19.934 --> 14:22.033
YES, BUT THE LYRICS
DON'T MAKE ANY SENSE.

14:22.100 --> 14:23.033
I MEAN IT DOES

14:23.100 --> 14:24.600
♪ MIAMI IS NICE ♪

14:24.667 --> 14:28.133
♪ SO I'LL SAY IT TWICE ♪

14:28.200 --> 14:31.533
OH, I SEE YOUR POINT.

14:31.967 --> 14:33.200
WELL, WHAT ABOUT THIS.

14:33.266 --> 14:34.934
♪ MIAMI IS NICE ♪

14:35.000 --> 14:36.934
♪ SO I'LL SAY IT THRICE ♪

14:38.166 --> 14:39.900
THRICE. WHO THE
HELL SAYS THRICE?

14:39.967 --> 14:41.567
IT'S A WORD.

14:41.633 --> 14:44.400
SO IS INTRAUTERINE.

14:49.400 --> 14:51.700
BUT DOES NOT BELONG IN A SONG.

14:55.934 --> 14:57.734
♪ MIAMI... ♪

14:57.800 --> 15:02.767
♪ YOU'RE CUTER THAN
AN INTRAUTERINE... ♪

15:09.400 --> 15:12.033
DO WE HAVE AN ORANGE JUICE LEFT?

15:21.166 --> 15:24.133
NO, WE'RE ALL OUT.

15:30.333 --> 15:33.867
HONESTLY,
SOPHIA, YOU THINK
WE ONLY FIGHT.

15:33.934 --> 15:36.000
I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

15:36.066 --> 15:37.934
WE ALSO TALK
ABOUT SEX.

15:40.533 --> 15:42.367
WE ALREADY TALKED
ABOUT SEX.

15:42.433 --> 15:43.834
I'M SHOCKED.

15:45.433 --> 15:47.867
MA, YOU'RE GOING
TO MISS US.

15:47.934 --> 15:50.100
WE HAD SOME
GOOD TIMES.

15:50.166 --> 15:51.834
PLENTY OF HEADACHES TOO.

15:51.900 --> 15:56.500
YOU HAVE TO ADMIT
IT'S NEVER DULL
AROUND HERE.

15:59.066 --> 16:00.333
AAH!

16:02.734 --> 16:05.166
YOU SHOT MY VASE.

16:06.266 --> 16:08.633
I HEARD FOOTSTEPS,
A MAN'S VOICE,

16:08.700 --> 16:09.734
AND THE ALARM
WENT OFF.

16:09.800 --> 16:12.467
LESTER ACCIDENTALLY
SET OFF THE ALARM.

16:12.533 --> 16:13.667
I'M SORRY.

16:13.734 --> 16:15.800
YOU SHOT MY VASE.

16:15.867 --> 16:17.233
I DIDN'T SHOOT LESTER.

16:17.300 --> 16:20.400
I'D RATHER
YOU SHOT LESTER.

16:20.467 --> 16:23.467
I THINK I'LL PASS
ON THE NIGHTCAP,
BLANCHE.

16:23.533 --> 16:24.900
GO HOME,
YOU FOOL.

16:24.967 --> 16:25.900
WHAT HAPPENED?

16:25.967 --> 16:27.867
SHE SHOT MY VASE!

16:27.934 --> 16:30.333
THANK GOD.
I HATED THAT THING.

16:32.133 --> 16:34.033
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
SHOOTING?

16:34.100 --> 16:35.266
ARE YOU CRAZY?

16:35.333 --> 16:37.467
I HEARD ROBBERS.

16:37.533 --> 16:40.367
I MANAGED TO LIVE
80...81 YEARS.

16:40.433 --> 16:43.867
I SURVIVED PNEUMONIA,
TWO OPERATIONS, A STROKE.

16:43.934 --> 16:45.133
ONE NIGHT I'LL BELCH,

16:45.200 --> 16:47.934
AND STABLE MABEL
WILL BLOW MY HEAD OFF.

16:48.900 --> 16:51.367
THERE'S A MAN
IN YOUR BED.

16:55.333 --> 16:57.700
OH, SOPHIA,
THERE'S NOT.

16:57.767 --> 16:59.000
WHY YOU DEVIL, YOU.

16:59.066 --> 17:02.633
SO THAT WAS
WHAT WE HEARD, ROSE.

17:03.934 --> 17:05.500
ROSE GOT LUCKY.

17:05.567 --> 17:06.867
NOT SO LUCKY.

17:06.934 --> 17:08.200
THE MAN IN YOUR BED
IS DEAD.

17:11.800 --> 17:12.767
WHAT?

17:12.834 --> 17:13.767
DEAD.

17:13.834 --> 17:15.333
OH, SOPHIA.

17:15.400 --> 17:18.100
HE'S NOT DEAD.
I WAS JUST IN THERE.

17:18.166 --> 17:20.567
I PUT BACK
YOUR LAUNDRY.

17:20.633 --> 17:23.233
I SEE HIM,
S0 I INTRODUCE MYSELF.

17:23.300 --> 17:24.834
HE DOESN'T ANSWER.

17:24.900 --> 17:25.867
HE'S DEAD.

17:25.934 --> 17:28.266
HE--HE'S SHY.

17:28.333 --> 17:29.567
HE'S VERY SHY.

17:29.633 --> 17:32.367
DIDN'T SOUND SO SHY
LAST NIGHT.

17:32.433 --> 17:35.033
LET A DEAD GUY LIE THERE.

17:35.100 --> 17:36.633
IT'S GOING TO BE 98 TODAY.

17:36.700 --> 17:38.233
IT WON'T BE PRETTY.

17:40.433 --> 17:43.100
OH, I'M SURE
HE'S NOT DEAD.

17:43.166 --> 17:44.200
ROSE, GO LOOK.

17:44.266 --> 17:47.000
HE'S SLEEPING.
I DON'T WANT
TO WAKE HIM.

17:47.066 --> 17:49.300
LIGHT FIRECRACKERS
IN HIS NOSTRILS.

17:49.367 --> 17:50.900
YOU WON'T WAKE HIM.

17:51.266 --> 17:52.500
BLANCHE DEVEREAUX.

17:52.567 --> 17:54.166
JUST A MOMENT.

18:05.233 --> 18:07.300
OH, MY GOD.

18:10.367 --> 18:12.667
MY REAR TIRES
HAVE LESS PRESSURE
IN THEM.

18:17.233 --> 18:18.367
I'M READY.

18:21.166 --> 18:24.567
THE MOON IS HANGING
AWFUL LOW IN THE SKY,

18:24.633 --> 18:26.166
ISN'T IT, BUSTY?

18:27.100 --> 18:28.166
JOSIE.

18:29.467 --> 18:30.967
IT SURE IS, BIFF.

18:31.033 --> 18:33.367
MAKES ME
WANT TO KISS YOU.

18:33.433 --> 18:35.233
MIND YOUR MANNERS, BIFF.

18:35.300 --> 18:37.400
WE'RE AT
THE JULY 4th PICNIC.

18:37.467 --> 18:38.834
THE WHOLE TOWN'S HERE.

18:38.900 --> 18:40.867
COME AWAY WITH ME.

18:40.934 --> 18:42.567
BUT YOU'RE
A DRIFTER, BIFF.

18:42.633 --> 18:45.367
I CAN'T
JUST PULL UP STAKES.

18:45.433 --> 18:47.333
PLEASE RECONSIDER.

18:47.400 --> 18:49.133
YOU'RE
THE PRETTIEST GIRL
IN THE COUNTY.

18:49.200 --> 18:51.367
I NEED TO HAVE
YOUR ANSWER NOW.

18:51.433 --> 18:53.767
WHAT'S IT
GOING TO BE?

18:53.834 --> 18:56.233
I WANT YOU
TO TAKE ME.

18:56.300 --> 18:58.000
[LEAKING AIR]

18:58.066 --> 19:01.867
OH.

19:01.934 --> 19:03.467
BLANCHE, I'M SORRY.

19:09.033 --> 19:11.100
SEE, SOPHIA, WE HAVE
GREAT TIMES TOGETHER.

19:11.166 --> 19:13.834
IT JUST WON'T BE
THE SAME.

19:13.900 --> 19:15.867
THIS ISN'T EASY
FOR ME, EITHER,

19:15.934 --> 19:20.333
BUT I HAVE TO DO
WHAT I HAVE TO DO.

19:20.400 --> 19:23.467
WHAT IS IT
I HAVE TO DO?

19:26.967 --> 19:28.734
YOU'RE LEAVING.

19:28.800 --> 19:29.934
THEN I BETTER PACK.

19:34.533 --> 19:37.467
WHAT I'M GOING TO
MISS ABOUT SOPHIA MOST

19:37.533 --> 19:39.400
IS ALL THAT
GOOD ADVICE.

19:39.467 --> 19:42.467
SHE HAS LOTS
TO DRAW ON.

19:42.533 --> 19:45.400
IF SHE DOESN'T HAVE
ANYTHING TO DRAW ON,

19:45.467 --> 19:46.967
SHE MAKES IT UP.

19:48.000 --> 19:49.633
SICILY, 1912.

19:49.700 --> 19:51.200
PICTURE THIS.

19:51.266 --> 19:52.800
TWO YOUNG GIRLS,

19:52.867 --> 19:55.300
BEST FRIENDS,
WHO SHARED
THREE THINGS...

19:55.367 --> 19:58.800
A PIZZA RECIPE,
SOME DOUGH,
AND A DREAM.

19:59.834 --> 20:01.066
EVERYTHING
IS GOING GREAT,

20:01.133 --> 20:04.233
UNTIL ONE DAY,
A FAST-TALKING
PEPPERONI SALESMAN

20:04.300 --> 20:06.333
GALLOPS INTO TOWN.

20:07.367 --> 20:08.967
OF COURSE, BOTH GIRLS
WERE IMPRESSED.

20:09.033 --> 20:10.200
HE DATES ONE
ONE NIGHT,

20:10.266 --> 20:12.233
THE OTHER
THE NEXT NIGHT.

20:12.300 --> 20:16.867
PRETTY SOON,
HE DRIVES A WEDGE
BETWEEN THEM.

20:16.934 --> 20:18.400
BEFORE YOU KNOW IT,

20:18.467 --> 20:21.900
THE PIZZA SUFFERS,
THE BUSINESS SUFFERS,
THE FRIENDSHIP SUFFERS.

20:21.967 --> 20:24.867
THE GIRLS PART COMPANY
AND HEAD FOR AMERICA,

20:24.934 --> 20:27.667
NEVER TO SEE
ONE ANOTHER AGAIN.

20:27.734 --> 20:29.400
ROSE...

20:29.467 --> 20:32.367
ONE OF THOSE GIRLS
WAS ME.

20:32.433 --> 20:35.633
THE OTHER ONE
YOU PROBABLY KNOW
AS MAMA CELESTE.

20:39.700 --> 20:41.433
MA, WHY DIDN'T YOU
USE YOUR KEY?

20:41.500 --> 20:43.834
I LEFT IT.
IT WOULD WEIGH ME DOWN.

20:45.600 --> 20:47.200
HOW DID YOU DO?

20:47.266 --> 20:49.367
GREAT. EASILY
A PERSONAL BEST.

20:49.433 --> 20:50.700
TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED.

20:50.767 --> 20:52.100
IT WAS ELECTRIC.

20:52.166 --> 20:54.066
THE STARTER
FIRED HIS PISTOL,

20:54.133 --> 20:55.233
AND LIKE A SHOT,

20:55.300 --> 20:57.266
I LEFT HALF MY COMPETITION
IN THE DUST.

20:57.333 --> 20:58.967
THAT FAST?

20:59.033 --> 21:00.533
IT WAS
THE OVER 80 CATEGORY.

21:00.600 --> 21:03.600
MOST DROPPED
FROM FRIGHT.

21:04.367 --> 21:06.367
YOU'RE KIDDING.

21:06.433 --> 21:09.667
PLEASE. THERE'S
A NATURAL BUILD
TO THESE STORIES.

21:09.734 --> 21:10.700
SORRY.

21:10.767 --> 21:12.600
SO, FINALLY,

21:12.667 --> 21:14.233
THE RACE WAS UNDERWAY.

21:14.300 --> 21:15.433
I START OFF SLOW.

21:15.500 --> 21:17.433
I'M CAGEY,
LIKE A PANTHER.

21:17.500 --> 21:19.467
WHEN THE TIME IS RIGHT,
I POUNCE.

21:19.533 --> 21:20.834
THE CROWD IS STANDING.

21:20.900 --> 21:23.834
SOPHIA!

21:23.900 --> 21:27.800
MY HEART IS POUNDING
IN MY EARS.

21:27.867 --> 21:30.533
BUT, THEN AGAIN,
IT ALWAYS DOES.

21:31.667 --> 21:33.066
I SAW THE FINISH LINE.

21:33.133 --> 21:35.667
IT WAS 200-300
YARDS AWAY.

21:35.734 --> 21:37.166
THEN IT HAPPENED.

21:37.233 --> 21:38.667
WHAT EVERY RUNNER DREADS.

21:38.734 --> 21:40.767
I HIT THE WALL.

21:40.834 --> 21:43.100
YOU RAN
OUT OF STEAM.

21:43.166 --> 21:45.867
NO. I ACTUALLY
HIT A WALL.

21:45.934 --> 21:47.800
IN SICILY,
WE NEVER WENT
TO THE DOCTOR.

21:47.867 --> 21:49.800
WE WENT
TO WIDOW CARAVELLI.

21:49.867 --> 21:52.967
WHATEVER YOU HAD,
SHE HAD A CURE.

21:53.033 --> 21:56.233
SHE WAS BEST KNOWN
FOR THIS GREEN SALVE

21:56.300 --> 21:58.200
FOR EAR INFECTIONS.

21:58.266 --> 22:00.633
ONE DAY,
SHE GAVE A BATCH
TO SALVADOR,

22:00.700 --> 22:01.700
THE VILLAGE IDIOT.

22:03.800 --> 22:05.333
HE MISUNDERSTOOD
THE DIRECTIONS

22:05.400 --> 22:07.200
AND PUT IT
ON HIS LINGUINE

22:07.266 --> 22:09.066
INSTEAD OF
IN HIS EAR.

22:17.367 --> 22:18.967
I GUESS
IF YOU'RE AN IDIOT

22:19.033 --> 22:20.033
WITH A HEARING PROBLEM,

22:20.100 --> 22:22.633
YOU DO THINGS LIKE THAT.

22:23.367 --> 22:26.400
IT WASN'T SUCH
A BAD THING TO DO.

22:26.467 --> 22:27.967
THE STUFF
TASTED GREAT,

22:28.033 --> 22:30.467
AND SALVADOR DECIDED
TO MARKET IT.

22:30.533 --> 22:33.066
AT FIRST, IT DIDN'T
MOVE SO WELL.

22:33.133 --> 22:35.200
"LINGUINE
WITH EAR SALVE"
ON A MENU

22:35.266 --> 22:37.800
DOESN'T LOOK
TOO APPETIZING.

22:37.867 --> 22:41.934
BUT ONCE HE CHANGED
IT TO "PESTO SAUCE,"

22:42.000 --> 22:43.834
IT MOVED
LIKE HOT CAKES.

22:43.900 --> 22:45.600
YOU'RE MAKING THIS UP.

22:45.667 --> 22:46.834
SO WHAT? I'M OLD.

22:46.900 --> 22:48.467
I'M SUPPOSED
TO BE COLORFUL.

22:50.533 --> 22:52.734
I'M GOING
TO MISS HER.

22:52.800 --> 22:55.867
ME TOO.

22:56.834 --> 22:59.300
I'M NOT GOING
TO STAND FOR IT.

22:59.367 --> 23:03.800
I'M TELLING HER
WE NEED HER
MORE THAN PHIL.

23:03.867 --> 23:05.367
FORGET IT.

23:05.433 --> 23:06.767
HER MIND IS MADE UP.

23:06.834 --> 23:09.467
SHE'S SAID IT 100 TIMES.

23:09.533 --> 23:11.967
I'M STAYING. GOOD NIGHT.

23:12.033 --> 23:13.000
WAIT A MINUTE.

23:13.066 --> 23:16.133
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
YOU'RE STAYING?

23:16.200 --> 23:17.133
WHAT'S THE PROBLEM?

23:17.200 --> 23:19.633
YOU ALREADY RENTED
MY ROOM?

23:19.700 --> 23:22.900
WHAT CHANGED
YOUR MIND?

23:22.967 --> 23:27.100
I JUST GOT
OFF THE PHONE
WITH PHIL'S WIFE.

23:27.166 --> 23:28.166
SHE'S BACK,
POOR THING.

23:28.233 --> 23:30.033
POOR THING?

23:30.100 --> 23:33.667
SHE FOUND OUT
SHE COULDN'T DO
BETTER THAN PHIL.

23:35.166 --> 23:37.133
NOT A STORYBOOK ROMANCE,

23:37.200 --> 23:39.233
BUT AN ENDING'S
AN ENDING.

23:39.300 --> 23:42.900
WE'RE SO GLAD
YOU'RE STAYING.

23:42.967 --> 23:44.367
WHEN WE THOUGHT
YOU WERE LEAVING,

23:44.433 --> 23:46.700
WE STARTED TALKING
ABOUT THE TIMES WE SHARED.

23:46.767 --> 23:49.400
IT BROUGHT BACK MEMORIES.

23:49.467 --> 23:51.667
IT WOULDN'T BE
THE SAME WITHOUT YOU.

23:51.734 --> 23:54.500
HEY, DON'T
OVER DRAMATIZE.

23:54.567 --> 23:57.633
THINGS AREN'T SO TERRIFIC
AROUND HERE.

23:58.867 --> 23:59.900
THE HELL THEY'RE NOT.

23:59.967 --> 24:01.433
THINGS ARE TERRIFIC
AROUND HERE!
